wikipedia_page.main: William Borradaile (10 July 1792 – 16 March 1838) was an English amateur cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1815 to 1832.  Mainly associated with Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC), he made 3 known appearances in first-class matches.  He played for the Gentlemen in the 1832 Gentlemen v Players match.
